  "sourceNotes": "Churros are a Spanish and Portuguese fried dough pastry with roots in the Iberian peninsula. The exact origin is debated; one account traces them to Portuguese sailors who adapted a form of youtiao (Chinese fried dough) encountered on trade routes in the sixteenth century. By the nineteenth century churros were established as a Spanish street food, sold by churrerias. The combination of churros with thick chocolate sauce (chocolate con churros) became the standard form in Spain and spread through Latin America, where regional variations developed.",
