  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Oil temperature is the single most important variable. At 180°C, churros cook in about 3 minutes and emerge golden and crisp. Below 170°C they absorb oil and turn greasy; above 190°C they brown on the outside before the centre cooks. Use a sugar thermometer and let the oil recover between batches: adding cold dough drops the temperature, and the next batch should wait until the thermometer reads 180°C again."
          }
        ]
      },
